WEBVTT

00:48.173 --> 00:52.177
Would a shrieking spider hawkhave eight wings or eight talons?

00:52.678 --> 00:53.971
What do you think, Xandra?

00:56.014 --> 00:57.015
Xandra?

00:59.434 --> 01:03.105
Wolfy,I can't decide which leaves to bring.

01:03.188 --> 01:04.272
Can you help?

01:04.355 --> 01:08.318
This one? This one? This one? This one?

01:08.402 --> 01:10.863
This one? This one? This one? This one?

01:11.780 --> 01:13.323
This one?

01:13.991 --> 01:17.119
It's an impossible choice.Why don't you take both?

01:17.703 --> 01:18.996
What a good idea.

01:21.874 --> 01:23.417
Are you okay, Xandra?

01:24.168 --> 01:25.752
What are you looking at?

01:25.836 --> 01:28.964
Wow. Are those your parents? Can I see?

01:29.047 --> 01:31.049
There's nothing to see.

01:31.133 --> 01:33.760
-Sprout, are you ready to go yet?-Almost.

01:36.305 --> 01:39.683
Sprout, aren't there any leavesat your parents' house?

01:39.766 --> 01:43.270
Of course. There's green onesand red ones and yellow ones--

01:43.854 --> 01:45.606
And little baby ones.

01:45.689 --> 01:49.359
You see, every Elderspryte Day,we hang up all the prettiest leaves,

01:49.443 --> 01:53.697
and then we sing songs and play games,and Grandmother tells stories.

01:53.780 --> 01:55.324
That sounds amazing.

01:56.450 --> 02:00.120
Wolfy, you should come homefor Elderspryte Day with us.

02:00.204 --> 02:03.624
Wow, really?Are you sure your parents won't mind?

02:03.707 --> 02:06.335
Of course not.You'll be one of the family.

02:06.418 --> 02:07.794
Just like Xandra.

02:11.089 --> 02:13.926
So, what is Elderspryte Day, exactly?

02:14.009 --> 02:17.763
Everyone has their own traditions,but it's a day when every spryte goes home

02:17.846 --> 02:20.682
and celebratesthe oldest spryte in their family.

02:20.766 --> 02:24.019
-That must be hard for you.-What? Why?

02:26.855 --> 02:28.815
The Figworts are my family.

02:29.650 --> 02:30.651
Come on, Sprout.

02:30.734 --> 02:32.444
They'll be worried if we're late.

02:40.494 --> 02:43.372
I can't wait for you to meet everyone,Wolfy.

02:43.455 --> 02:46.124
Mum, Dad, Grandmother…

02:46.208 --> 02:47.835
You already met Flora.

02:47.918 --> 02:50.254
There's Ivy, and there's Clover,

02:50.337 --> 02:54.800
Shrub, Violet, Petal,Juniper, Rooty, Azalea,

02:54.883 --> 02:57.135
Aunt Wisteria, she's a hoot.

02:57.219 --> 02:59.429
And then there's Hoot, my cousin.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.223
-And my other cousin---There it is.

03:02.015 --> 03:03.559
Figwort Farm.

03:06.019 --> 03:08.939
I bet we'll get there quickerif we cut through these bushes.

03:09.022 --> 03:10.315
Never leave the path!

03:11.275 --> 03:14.236
Never leave the path.

03:18.282 --> 03:21.577
Sorry. It's nice and safe on the path.

03:25.330 --> 03:28.458
-Grandmother!-Sprout, dear.

03:29.877 --> 03:32.796
It's so good to see you.

03:32.880 --> 03:37.551
And Xandra. Get over hereand give your grandmother a hug.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.643
Grandmother, this is our friend Wolfboy.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.478
Happy Elderspryte Day.

03:49.271 --> 03:53.108
It's tomorrow, dear. But I'll take it.

03:53.609 --> 03:57.196
Don't worry, everyone. It's just Sprout.

03:57.779 --> 03:59.615
You can all come out.

04:00.199 --> 04:03.160
-Thank goodness.-Sprout! Great to see you!

04:03.243 --> 04:04.870
Sprouty!

04:04.953 --> 04:07.289
How do you do? I'm Sprout's mum.

04:07.372 --> 04:09.208
Nice to meet you, Mrs. Figwort.

04:09.291 --> 04:11.752
Hush now. You must call me Perennia.

04:14.505 --> 04:15.797
Now, girls, girls!

04:15.881 --> 04:18.050
Your poor brother's had a long trip.

04:19.343 --> 04:21.470
How many sisters does Sprout have?

04:21.553 --> 04:22.721
Twenty-three.

04:23.472 --> 04:24.640
Twenty-four.

04:27.851 --> 04:31.522
Bud Figwort. Welcome to Figwort Farm.

04:32.105 --> 04:36.652
Right. Come on, come on.Let's troddle in and get you all fed.

04:37.653 --> 04:40.239
You're so lucky to have such a big family.

04:40.322 --> 04:42.407
It was always just me and Mum and--

04:45.244 --> 04:46.870
I didn't mean lucky…

04:46.954 --> 04:50.582
No, it's okay. I am lucky. I…

04:52.543 --> 04:53.961
I gotta go unpack.

04:59.258 --> 05:01.093
I hope I didn't upset her.

05:01.176 --> 05:03.178
I think she's okay.

05:03.262 --> 05:06.598
Elderspryte Dayis always kinda tough for her.

05:06.682 --> 05:09.893
She never talks about her parents,does she?

05:09.977 --> 05:13.063
Not really. Not even with me.

05:13.146 --> 05:16.650
I hope she knows that she could talk to usif she wanted to.

05:18.735 --> 05:19.820
Hi there.

05:21.029 --> 05:22.281
I'm Juniper.

05:22.364 --> 05:24.241
Wanna see my bug collection?

05:31.957 --> 05:35.294
Hey! He's my friend, Juniper.

05:39.715 --> 05:41.008
Hi, Flora.

05:41.091 --> 05:45.888
How do you know Flora?She doesn't even have any bugs.

05:46.388 --> 05:48.599
We met in the woods, battling disarrays.

05:49.558 --> 05:50.976
Doing what?

05:51.059 --> 05:52.311
Disarrays?

05:52.811 --> 05:55.147
I thinkyou're remembering that wrong, Wolfboy.

05:55.230 --> 05:56.481
I'm sorry, Xandra.

05:56.565 --> 05:59.526
I didn't mean to leave you out.You were brave too.

05:59.610 --> 06:03.572
No, no. That was all you, Wolfy.

06:03.655 --> 06:06.408
Sprout and I know betterthan to mess with disarrays.

06:06.491 --> 06:08.827
I should jolly well think so too.

06:09.828 --> 06:12.748
"Run, run, run away"…

06:12.831 --> 06:15.334
"So you can run away another day."

06:15.417 --> 06:16.460
Run away?

06:16.960 --> 06:20.756
Sprout, haven't you taught your friendany of our family mottoes?

06:21.757 --> 06:25.052
Well, I did tell him to stay on the path.

06:25.135 --> 06:27.221
Well, yes, that's a classic.

06:27.304 --> 06:30.224
I know! "Get inside, it's time to hide."

06:31.141 --> 06:32.226
Good one, June.

06:32.309 --> 06:35.270
"If in danger at all, curl into a ball."

06:35.896 --> 06:37.105
Now we're cooking.

06:49.826 --> 06:54.456
Hey, why did you say I was the only onewho battled the disarrays?

06:54.540 --> 06:56.166
You two were brave as well.

06:56.250 --> 07:00.254
Yeah, I'm sorry about that.I didn't want Sprout to get in trouble.

07:00.337 --> 07:03.549
The Figworts take their family mottoesvery seriously.

07:04.174 --> 07:07.177
But it's like they thinkbeing brave is a bad thing.

07:07.261 --> 07:08.637
That's the Figwort way.

07:10.055 --> 07:12.015
But you don't believe that.

07:12.099 --> 07:14.017
You're the bravest spryte I know.

07:15.018 --> 07:18.230
Look, I don't want the Figwortsto worry about me.

07:18.313 --> 07:20.023
They've already done so much.

07:20.107 --> 07:22.025
But that's not who you are.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.903
You're going to bea legendary guardian spryte one day,

07:24.987 --> 07:26.446
just like your parents.

07:34.246 --> 07:35.831
Look, I'm sorry.

07:36.498 --> 07:41.879
I know you don't like talking about them.But I want you to know you can trust me.

07:42.546 --> 07:46.758
If you do ever wanna talk, well, I'm here.

07:58.145 --> 08:00.814
Okay, settle down, Figworts.

08:01.940 --> 08:05.903
It's timefor Grandmother's Elderspryte Eve story.

08:06.486 --> 08:08.405
So exciting. Favorite time.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.781
Shh, everyone.

08:10.449 --> 08:15.245
I'm so happy to seeall of your smiling faces.

08:16.163 --> 08:18.624
And I know Grandfather Figwort

08:18.707 --> 08:23.045
would be so proudof how our family has grown.

08:24.379 --> 08:26.131
Grandpa Figwort.

08:26.215 --> 08:28.884
What story would you like to hearthis year?

08:28.967 --> 08:30.177
The Petrified Petal!

08:30.260 --> 08:32.011
-Horrified Hydrangea.-Timid Tulip.

08:32.095 --> 08:34.640
-The Fearful Fern.-Meek Myrtle's Misadventures.

08:34.722 --> 08:37.476
-The Ladybug Who Lied!-The Tale of the Cowardly Crocus.

08:37.558 --> 08:38.644
The Fearful Fern!

08:38.727 --> 08:40.604
I'd like to request a story.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.688
Of course, dear.

08:42.773 --> 08:43.774
What'll it be?

08:50.405 --> 08:52.074
I'd like to hear

08:52.783 --> 08:54.910
the story of the Great Betrayal.

08:58.539 --> 09:00.457
No, Xandra, no.

09:00.541 --> 09:03.001
-I can't believe it.-Xandra's gonna--

09:03.585 --> 09:04.878
Hush now.

09:05.379 --> 09:07.172
Good choice, Xandra.

09:08.841 --> 09:12.344
A decade ago, the world was in turmoil.

09:13.720 --> 09:19.059
The wicked disarrays were growing moredangerous and destructive by the day.

09:20.060 --> 09:24.106
Their chaotic ways threatenedthe very existence of the world

09:24.189 --> 09:27.609
we sprytes worked so hard to create.

09:28.318 --> 09:30.195
Rather than lose hope,

09:30.279 --> 09:33.532
brave guardian sprytes,like Xandra's parents,

09:33.615 --> 09:35.617
stepped up to save us.

09:36.702 --> 09:43.333
They led the charge in a heroic attemptto rid the world of disarrays for good.

09:44.126 --> 09:49.047
The guardians fought valiantlyfor all those who could not fight.

09:49.631 --> 09:54.678
They used every ounce of their strengthto push the disarrays back.

09:55.179 --> 09:59.266
But just when they wereon the brink of victory,

09:59.349 --> 10:01.435
they were betrayed

10:01.935 --> 10:06.773
by a spryte named Nyx.

10:06.857 --> 10:08.233
Nyx!

10:09.401 --> 10:13.322
Nyx's mightwas only matched by her malice.

10:15.240 --> 10:19.453
She fought with the disarraysagainst her own kind.

10:21.121 --> 10:24.374
Her treachery turned the tideof the battle,

10:25.042 --> 10:28.128
and the disarrays escaped.

10:31.048 --> 10:32.716
The war was won.

10:33.217 --> 10:39.431
And Nyx was banished for her crimes,imprisoned forever in the disarray realm.

10:40.307 --> 10:43.393
But the damage was done.

10:47.064 --> 10:52.277
Two very brave sprytes were lost that day.

11:00.369 --> 11:02.454
I hate to say it, but--

11:02.538 --> 11:03.580
I know.

11:03.664 --> 11:08.043
"If guardians lived like Figworts, therewould be a lot more guardians around."

11:09.253 --> 11:10.254
No, no.

11:10.337 --> 11:13.048
Actually, I was going to say it's bedtime.

11:13.549 --> 11:15.217
You heard him, off to bed.

11:15.300 --> 11:18.929
But don't forget to give your grandmothera hug and a kiss.

11:19.012 --> 11:22.266
Xandra, you can go first, sweetheart.

11:24.226 --> 11:26.436
Thank you for the story, Grandmother.

11:26.520 --> 11:27.938
You know what I think?

11:28.730 --> 11:35.070
If guardians lived like Figworts,there would be a lot fewer Figworts.

11:43.495 --> 11:46.415
I'm sorry. I can come back later.

11:46.498 --> 11:48.417
I really miss them sometimes.

11:50.294 --> 11:52.045
All the time, actually.

12:06.435 --> 12:08.937
I bet they're really proud of you.

12:16.111 --> 12:18.655
You must have some great storiesabout them.

12:19.323 --> 12:21.700
I do know a good one.

12:22.201 --> 12:26.330
Once, when they were on patrolin the darkest corner of the Factory,

12:26.413 --> 12:29.416
they were ambushedby a pack of hungry scrawmongers.

12:29.499 --> 12:31.627
Scrawmongers? What are they?

12:32.127 --> 12:34.046
They're the worst kind of disarray.

12:34.129 --> 12:37.549
Gnashing teeth,eyes that bore right into your soul.

12:37.633 --> 12:40.511
But my parents,they weren't afraid one bit.

12:40.594 --> 12:43.514
Wow. They were so brave.

12:43.597 --> 12:44.681
Yeah.

12:44.765 --> 12:47.351
My parents weren't afraid of anything.

12:55.651 --> 12:57.194
-Excuse me!-It's my turn!

12:57.277 --> 12:59.154
-No!-Mum!

12:59.238 --> 13:00.781
-Give me that!-Mum!

13:00.864 --> 13:02.574
-Make me a biscuit!-Mum!

13:03.742 --> 13:05.285
Mum?

13:08.622 --> 13:09.831
-Mum!-I wanna see that.

13:10.415 --> 13:11.458
Excuse me!

13:11.542 --> 13:13.460
Make me a biscuit!

13:13.544 --> 13:16.004
-Does anyone want to play?-Who ate all the blue mash?

13:21.385 --> 13:22.553
Everybody ready?

13:23.387 --> 13:26.974
One, two, three, go!

13:27.850 --> 13:31.937
And the small fleet set sailacross the treacherous sea.

13:32.020 --> 13:34.356
Beneath the surface lurk sea dragons

13:34.439 --> 13:38.068
and octopusesand krakens of the worst kind.

13:44.616 --> 13:47.119
You're really good at making stuff.

13:47.202 --> 13:50.747
I would be if I knew how I was doing it.

13:57.337 --> 14:00.424
What's that, Xandra?You need help? Be right there.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.012
You need help?

14:05.679 --> 14:07.139
I don't need help.

14:08.348 --> 14:12.019
Easy does it. Easy does it.Just don't look down.

14:12.102 --> 14:13.103
Can I help?

14:13.937 --> 14:17.316
Let's leave the aerial stuntsto the daredevils, shall we?

14:17.399 --> 14:21.028
Besides,that's much too scary for you, Sprout.

14:25.616 --> 14:27.826
Oh, Sprout.

14:32.497 --> 14:35.042
Be sure you roll out the mudnice and flat.

14:35.125 --> 14:37.503
Do you need any helpwith the mud dumplings?

14:38.003 --> 14:40.547
Thanks, Sprout.We've got all the help we need.

14:49.765 --> 14:53.435
You know,Grandmother asked about her crown.

14:53.519 --> 14:56.897
Oh, dear. She's lost her crown again?

14:56.980 --> 14:59.149
I bet your father hid it away.

14:59.233 --> 15:02.277
He's always worried it'll attractthe you-know-what.

15:21.922 --> 15:23.549
Look what we made.

15:25.342 --> 15:29.555
It's a very special Elderspryte Daydecoration for you, Grandmother Figwort.

15:31.598 --> 15:33.183
Thank you, dear.

15:33.267 --> 15:38.313
Look at me.I'm finally starting to look festive.

15:38.397 --> 15:41.108
But there's one thing missing.

15:44.111 --> 15:46.029
My crown.

15:46.905 --> 15:50.701
I can't believe it. I thought it was lost.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.870
It was, but I found it.

15:54.621 --> 15:56.623
Thank you, Sprout.

15:56.707 --> 16:00.043
Elderspryte Day wouldn't be the samewithout it.

16:00.127 --> 16:03.505
-Is it a special crown?-Very special indeed.

16:03.589 --> 16:08.051
It's made from rare flowersthat only grow out in the bogmarsh.

16:08.135 --> 16:10.095
That's way off the path.

16:10.596 --> 16:15.559
Cypress, my late husband,he was quite the risk-taker.

16:16.101 --> 16:19.521
He snuck out into the bogmarshto find the flowers,

16:19.605 --> 16:22.649
and then he wove them together himself.

16:23.317 --> 16:25.986
That was how he won my heart.

16:27.487 --> 16:29.156
That's a lovely story.

16:29.656 --> 16:31.867
Not everyone thinks so.

16:32.534 --> 16:35.245
Good, you've found your crown.

16:35.329 --> 16:39.374
I was worried that no one would be able tofind it this time.

16:40.042 --> 16:41.710
Reckless spryte, my father,

16:41.793 --> 16:44.505
stomping around in the marsh like that,off the path.

16:44.588 --> 16:46.256
He was lucky to make it out alive.

16:46.340 --> 16:49.718
As for making a crown out ofthe bogmarsh beast's favorite flowers--

16:49.801 --> 16:51.094
The bogmarsh beast?

16:51.178 --> 16:54.848
What's it look like? How big is it?How many rows of teeth does it have?

16:55.349 --> 16:56.600
Let's go find it.

17:00.187 --> 17:03.565
Hey, are those mud dumplings I smell?

17:04.525 --> 17:06.818
Oh, my Cypress.

17:06.902 --> 17:09.530
There's never been a Figwortquite like him.

17:37.015 --> 17:39.101
What are you up to, Juniper?

17:39.184 --> 17:41.311
I'm making a hero's badge

17:42.020 --> 17:43.188
for Wolfboy.

17:50.112 --> 17:52.155
Is she always like this?

17:53.031 --> 17:56.827
Well, she's never made me a badge,

17:57.327 --> 18:00.163
but I guess I'm not special like you.

18:02.916 --> 18:04.126
What was that?

18:10.090 --> 18:12.968
The bogmarsh beast!

18:13.051 --> 18:15.095
That's the bogmarsh beast?

18:16.680 --> 18:19.433
It's smaller than I thought it would be.

18:24.771 --> 18:27.816
-Run, run, run away to live!-Sprout, wait.

18:27.900 --> 18:30.194
Run, run, run away!

18:31.695 --> 18:33.322
Remember your training.

18:33.405 --> 18:35.032
Everyone to the house tree.

18:35.115 --> 18:37.367
Shoo, shoo, you nasty beast.

18:41.413 --> 18:42.873
Grandmother!

18:46.418 --> 18:47.753
My crown!

18:47.836 --> 18:49.838
Stop right there, beast.

18:49.922 --> 18:53.217
Xandra, come inside. It's time to hide.

18:59.139 --> 19:00.516
We have to surround it.

19:02.768 --> 19:05.062
-Trip it with your vines, Sprout.-What?

19:05.145 --> 19:06.939
-Curl up in a ball.-Who?

19:07.022 --> 19:08.899
-Make yourself big to scare it.-When?

19:08.982 --> 19:10.859
Curl up in a ball!

19:12.152 --> 19:13.654
Sprout!

19:27.167 --> 19:28.710
Mummy's little Sproutling.

19:29.711 --> 19:33.757
You did good.You're no match for that beast.

19:36.635 --> 19:37.928
Are you all right?

19:38.887 --> 19:40.472
You'll get him next time.

19:40.556 --> 19:42.808
No, she's right.

19:42.891 --> 19:47.646
Maybe you or Xandra could have stopped it,but not me.

19:49.940 --> 19:51.066
Poor Sprout.

19:51.900 --> 19:55.070
I just wish there was somethingwe could do.

19:55.153 --> 19:58.240
Let me guess.You've got some cunning plan to help him.

19:58.323 --> 20:01.034
Of course I've got a cunning planto help him.

20:01.118 --> 20:05.289
And this particular plancalls for a game of hide-and-seek.

20:07.457 --> 20:08.458
Wow!

20:08.542 --> 20:12.337
I've never been the seeker before.How high should I count?

20:13.297 --> 20:16.175
Maybe you should justlist all your cousins again.

20:16.675 --> 20:17.843
Okay.

20:17.926 --> 20:22.055
Dahlia, Iris, Violet, Tulip, Barkly,

20:22.139 --> 20:25.392
Shrub, Myrtle, Petal, Daisy.

20:26.852 --> 20:29.021
You guys are terrible hiders.

20:29.855 --> 20:32.482
Hold on. We're not in the yard.

20:33.901 --> 20:35.569
We're not even on the path.

20:36.403 --> 20:38.614
This is the bogmarsh.

20:53.253 --> 20:54.880
I'm sorry we surprised you,

20:54.963 --> 20:56.798
-but Xandra and I---Mostly you.

20:56.882 --> 20:58.800
We thought it might cheer you up

20:58.884 --> 21:02.179
if we brought you out hereto collect those rare flowers.

21:02.262 --> 21:05.140
And we can make a new crownfor your grandmother.

21:09.311 --> 21:11.188
That's a nice idea,

21:11.271 --> 21:15.275
but I should get back to the path.

21:16.360 --> 21:18.612
I'm no Grandpa Cypress.

21:19.404 --> 21:21.823
No, you are brave, Sprout.

21:21.907 --> 21:25.827
You are Sprout,the tamer of explodeling rabbits.

21:25.911 --> 21:27.955
Master of the memory mites.

21:32.918 --> 21:36.255
Okay, I'll comeand make sure you two are safe.

21:36.338 --> 21:38.048
And then I'm going back.

21:44.513 --> 21:47.391
The red flowers mean we're near the water.

21:47.474 --> 21:50.936
And those vines only grownear the muddiest bogs.

21:51.478 --> 21:54.189
Which means we're in the right place.

21:54.815 --> 21:56.275
Look! There they are.

22:04.408 --> 22:05.617
Sprout?

22:06.910 --> 22:08.579
Bogmarsh beast!

22:09.997 --> 22:11.915
Run for the trees!

22:15.294 --> 22:17.588
It still has Grandmother's crown.

22:17.671 --> 22:20.340
Okay. Xandra, you go round the right.

22:20.424 --> 22:21.675
And, Sprout--

22:23.177 --> 22:26.388
Sprout, come on.We can still rescue the crown.

22:26.471 --> 22:28.932
What? No! Don't go near it.

22:29.016 --> 22:31.810
Nonsense. Come on, Xandra, charge!

22:32.394 --> 22:35.063
No! Wait! You have to watch out for the…

22:35.898 --> 22:37.191
marsh mud.

22:39.860 --> 22:42.237
Oh, no. No, no.

22:43.322 --> 22:45.115
What? That's not fair.

22:45.199 --> 22:47.075
How come he doesn't sink?

22:50.621 --> 22:52.873
Stay back. Stay back.

22:55.042 --> 22:56.919
Leave my friends alone.

22:57.961 --> 23:01.757
Wouldn't you rather have some nice,fresh flowers?

23:27.616 --> 23:28.742
Sprout,

23:28.825 --> 23:31.328
that was the bravest thing I've ever seen.

